  "title": "Setting custom/non search parameters url attributes while refining the search",
  "body": "I have a use case where I want to:\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget({\n  container: document.querySelector('#custom-widget'),\n  render: function(options) {\n    var link = document.createElement('a');\n    link.innerText = 'test';\n    link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n      e.preventDefault();\n      history.pushState(null, '', location.search + '&isCustom=true&test_custom=false');\n      options.helper.toggleRefine('brand', 'Samsung');\n      options.helper.search();\n    });\n    this.container.innerHTML = '';\n    this.container.appendChild(link);\n  }\n});\n```\n\nSo basically, it's a simple link, that when clicked, will refine the search while setting url custom attributes.\n\nIt works when clicking but if I click on back button then `&isCustom=true&test_custom=false` will still be in the url while they should not be here. I believe it's not really a bug, just the way things are working right now.\n\nDo we need a higher level API to be able to update the current url state or am I missing something?\n\n@bobylito Could you help me on this?\n",
